messages.message: Having a `#` (and probably other specials chars) in the file name causes upload error

@Subash @Aayush Is there a check on the UI for using `#` in a filename?
Because I also tried to upload a file with a name `US_Payslip_#3.pdf` , the API call that was sent to the backend was `https://aihub.dev.instabase.com/api/v2/zero-shot-idp/projects/0bb1f78c-11c5-4e99-823e-091cf0a35c0b/documents/US_Payslip_`. It seems like everything after a `#` is being sliced.
this is also an issue in Build. @Subash or @Aayush let me know if youâ€™re already looking into it otherwise I can make a ticket for build
